decks.notes: This Rakdos Aggro deck focuses on aggressive creature plays and disruption. It utilizes cards like Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer and Seasoned Pyromancer to pressure the opponent while also using cards like Grief and Thoughtseize to disrupt their plans. The inclusion of cards like Blood Moon and Magus of the Moon can also punish non-basic land heavy decks. With a mix of removal spells like Terminate and Lightning Bolt, this deck aims to quickly overwhelm the opponent and close out the game before they can establish their own game plan.

This deck focuses on utilizing powerful creatures with varying colors and abilities to quickly overwhelm the opponent and deal damage efficiently. By including Jegantha as a companion, the deck gains access to additional mana and a potential late-game advantage. With a mix of aggressive creatures like Nishoba Brawler and Territorial Kavu, along with versatile spells like Tribal Flames and Stubborn Denial, this deck aims to maintain board presence and pressure the opponent consistently. The mana base is carefully designed to support the diverse color requirements of the deck.
